<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 8:12PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern Towns
and central Union Counties through 845 PM EDT...
At 811 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Owltown to near Brasstown Bald. These storms were
nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Blairsville, Owltown, Blue Mountain Shelter, Vogel State Park,
Brasstown Bald, Track Rock, Mountain Scene and Woods Hole Shelter.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
